noun.name: suitcase
noun.discription: a piece of luggage designed to carry clothes and personal items

object1.name: backpack
object1.discription: in parallel with 'suitcase', is a bag with straps to be worn on the back, typically used for carrying books and other items

object2.name: briefcase
object2.discription: in parallel with 'suitcase', is a flat, rectangular case used for carrying documents and business materials

object3.name: duffel bag
object3.discription: in parallel with 'suitcase', is a large cylindrical bag made of thick fabric, often used for travel or sports equipment

object4.name: tote bag
object4.discription: in parallel with 'suitcase', is a large, open bag with parallel handles that emerge from the sides of its pouch

object5.name: garment bag
object5.discription: in parallel with 'suitcase', is a long, narrow bag designed to hold clothing, often used for formal wear

object6.name: carry-on
object6.discription: in parallel with 'suitcase', is a small piece of luggage that meets airline regulations for being carried on the plane

object7.name: trunk
object7.discription: in parallel with 'suitcase', is a large, sturdy box used for storage or transportation of goods, often found in vehicles or homes

object8.name: satchel
object8.discription: in parallel with 'suitcase', is a bag with a strap, typically worn over one shoulder, often used by students or professionals
